.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.DAYSINMONTH" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.daysInMonth \-
Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.daysInMonth
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]daysInMonth\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instances returns a positive integer
representing the number of days in the month of this date.
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
Note that the days in month is not always equal to the \f[CR]day\f[R] of
the last day of the month, in the rare case where a month may have a few
days skipped.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]daysInMonth\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using daysInMonth
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
console.log(date.daysInMonth); \f[I]// 31\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-02\-01\(dq);
console.log(date2.daysInMonth); \f[I]// 28; 2021 is not a leap year\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2020\-02\-01\(dq);
console.log(date3.daysInMonth); \f[I]// 29; 2020 is a leap year\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date4 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-04\-01[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
console.log(date4.month); \f[I]// 2\f[R]
console.log(date4.daysInMonth); \f[I]// 30; the Chinese 2nd month has 30 days\f[R]
.EE
.SS Changing to the second last day of the month
You can use \f[CR]daysInMonth\f[R] to change to the second last day of
the month:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] secondLastDay = date.with({ day: date.daysInMonth \- 1 });
console.log(secondLastDay.toString()); \f[I]// 2021\-07\-30\f[R]
.EE
.PP
This is not totally safe, though, because \f[CR]daysInMonth\f[R] is not
guaranteed to have any connection with the day index.
Here\(cqs a safer way to get the second last day:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] secondLastDay = date
  .with({ day: Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER })
  .subtract({ days: 1 });
console.log(secondLastDay.toString()); \f[I]// 2021\-07\-30\f[R]
.EE
